Hey there! I’m Jaki,(pronounced like Jackie) I decided to get approved to provide soundwave tattoos to everyday clients to help better serve my area. There’s not really any artists in Jacksonville that are certified through skinMotion to do these types of tattoos. Don’t hesitate to hit me up! I work in a professional shop atmosphere with proper licensing and sanitation practices.

**update 
I’d highly recommend messaging any literal artist with good linework in your area to do these tattoos- it seems the mass amount of emails I receive in regards to this company never want to wait to get the tattoo they request due to me being booked out months in advance. Any tattooer can get certified in this after a 10 minute test/video. This company will not allow me to delete/turn off my profile hence- why I’m writing this. 
Good luck and my apologies

Auch hier freue ich mich um jedes Stück Haut das ich mit meiner Kunst verziehren darf. Seit September 2016 bin ich im Stadtteil Laim zu finden.

_______________________

bio:
Ive been a professional Tattoo Artist for 16 years, with a focus in my own neo traditional-illustrative-new school. Super nerd, into all things pop culture, robots, monsters, cartoons, comics, etc. Apprenticed by Big Daddy Tray at Big Daddy's Tattoo in E-Town Kentucky in 2002. I currently own a small studio, "Tattoo KAIJU," in Bloomington Indiana, which also has a gallery where we host regular art shows, openings/events, and a small art goods gift shop with enamel pins, prints, stickers, toys, etc.   We offer up to a 75% cut to artists who show and sell at TK, student and military discounts, commission work, as well as many opportunities to be involved with group art shows, pop ups, and projects. My mission is to provide a clean, fun, and personal space that will highlight my aesthetic and the artwork of me, my peers, and the community.

bio: I am Jared Preslar and I began tattooing professionally in 1997, I hungered to be a tattoo artist from the age of 12. Art was always my passion, I loved to draw from a young age and later began to oil paint. I immediately fell in love with this medium and it has influenced my tattooing greatly. I have Jeff Gogue to thank for his time and sharing of knowledge, technique and experience, I may have never picked up an oil brush had it not been for him. Some of the artists whom have influenced my tattooing over the years have been Filip Leu, Guy Aitchison, Horiyoshi III, Shige, and Jeff Gogue to name a few. I have spent quite a few years traveling around the world, meeting and tattooing some very amazing people that of which I'm grateful for, I am however settling down from travel and am really focusing on refining/redesigning my art at this point. I am constantly focused on growing as an artist and as a person although I have a long way to go I have very high aspirations.

bio:
Tom Inkjet Hartmann,  Geboren 1978 in Johannesburg (Süd Afrika). Seit 1987 lebe ich in der schweiz. Mit Ca 12 Jahren habe ich zum 1.mal eine Tätowierung gesehen. Da ich schon immer leidenschaftlich zeichne war für mich sofort klar das tätowieren meine Berufung ist. 1995 hatte ich das grosse Glück dieses spezielle Handwerk zu erlernen. Seit dieser zeit mache ich nichts anderes. meine Stielrichtungen sind: hauptsächlich schwarz/weiss Schädel,bio-organic,Tier Portraits ,Fine-line,Dark-art…usw


My name is Tom Inkjet Hartmann. I was born in Johannesburg (South Africa) in 1978. I moved to Switzerland in 1987. At about 12 years old, I saw my first tattoo. Because As I always drew, tattooing should automatically become my passion In 1995, I was very lucky to be able to learn this art. And that's what I've been doing since then. My style rather black/white, skulls, bio-mechanicals ,animals portraits ,Fine-line, Dark-art. . . etc

Je m’appelle Tom Inkjet Hartmann. Je suis né à Johannesburg (Afrique du sud) en 1978. J’ai déménagé en Suisse en 1987. A environ 12 ans j’ai vu mon premier tatouage. Comme j’ai toujours dessiné, le tatouage devait automatiquement devenir ma passion. En 1995, j’ai eu la grande chance de pouvoir apprendre cet art. Et c’est ce que je fais depuis. Mon style est plutôt noir et blanc, des crânes, du bio-mécanique, les animaux, les portraits et le dark style.

address: 112 Riverside Lofts, Tygerfalls, Bellville, Cape town, Western Cape
bio:
The idea of “Moving Art” sparked while watching one of the first international tattoo shows in South Africa. With Support from her husband Matt and Sheradon’s artistic background she knew without a doubt that this is what she wanted to do. She then did a 6 months apprenticeship at Urban Ink with Tyrone De Bruin, then worked from home practicing for 3 years. After 3 years Moving Art Tattoos was finally registered as a professional tattoo studio in 2010. Since the shop opened in Edward Street there have been a lot of different artists and so a lot of experience was gained and the business grew until where we are today. We have a team that is now like family, we are ready for whats to come in the future.
Currently we are a team of 3 artists. Sheradon Brits is the owner and founder of Moving Art Tattoos, she is all hands on deck, a tattoo artist and body piercing artist. She founded the company in 2010 and has worked extremely hard to get the business where it is now which is a dependable reputable company giving a new and better impression of the tattoo scene that still gets frowned upon. Ettienne Roux joined our team in April 2017, he had his own tattoo studio in Rustenburg and he, as well as Shez has been tattooing just over 9 years. Both artists have insane talent and love challenges, they are always exploring new styles. Mckale Todd joined the team in November 2017 as a body piercing artist but has since started tattooing also and is currently our apprentice. All 3 artists love doing their custom designs. The team is excited about the business growing and expanding and can’t wait for new challenges and experiences.

address: 1418 N. Claiborne Ave., #5, New Orleans, Louisiana
bio: Mitch Black was born and raised in New Orleans, Louisiana. Due to hurricane Katrina in 2005, he was displaced to Miami during middle school. Although he has loved art his entire life, it was in Miami that Mitch started to notice and become fond of tattoos and the art, history, and culture that surrounded them. He basically got tattooed as often as possible and gained as much knowledge as he could from watching and talking with the artist who produced work on his body. At the age of 20, he moved back to his native city of New Orleans and spent the next 5 years drawing, painting murals, and doing graffiti before finally landing an apprenticeship at a tattoo shop in 2016. After a year and a half of taking shit from the elder artists, cleaning shop - top to bottom nearly everyday, and making countless store runs for the crew, he was finally able to pick up a machine and start honing in on the skills of the craft. After a few months of giving away free tattoos to any brave soul that would allow him to modify their body forever, he was officially licensed and started his career as a tattoo artist. Although the graffiti has drastically slowed down due to the birth of his beautiful baby girl, he still loves to paint murals and canvas, amongst other art projects outside of painting tattoo flash and drawing for clients at work.

address: 2900 Norwell Drive, upper level, Nanaimo, British Columbia
bio:
Maria has been artistically inclined her entire life and has developed her artistic skills in a variety of mediums. One of these mediums was a jewelry line which was sold across North America. Maria apprenticed with award winning Tattoo Artist Reginald Morrel, and has been tattooing professionally ever since. Her attention to detail is unsurpassed. Her philosophy is that you are commissioning a piece of artwork for your body, so it has to be perfect.

Designing your tattoo is a creative process that can take some time depending on the size and detail that you want. Maria likes to have you come in for a consultation to determine what exactly your thoughts are and how they can translate into a piece of wearable art. From there, any artwork that has inspired your tattoo is compiled into your own client file. A rough design is then composed and sent to you for your approval. Once your design is perfected and is ready to be inked, our private rooms assure that there will be no interruptions or distractions. Your appointment is all about you!

address: Rua Visconde de Pirajá, 318/206, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro
bio:
Em 21 de Janeiro de 1962, no Rio de Janeiro ás 23h45min, cheguei para mais uma vida com determinação e muita vontade de viver.

Um mês antes de meu renascimento minha mãe (a querida Didi) pensava em abortar, pois era seu terceiro filho e não se achava prepara para tal responsabilidade. Didi foi então ao médico, esse porém com todo carinho a explicou que o feto já possuia mãozinhas, dedinhos.. sensibilizando-a. Porém Didi não estava grávida como imaginava. Engravidou logo em seguida.

Com essa nova visão da vida que lhe foi dada, Didi completou sua gestação com todo amor que é sua essência. Didi então teve seu terceiro filho.

Eu.

​

Números

A primeira palavra que falei foi "dez", isso mesmo, um número, adoro números.. A partir dos quatro anos, antes de ingressar na escola assustava as pessoas quando falava números enormes, tipo um quinquilhão, trezentos e trinta quatrilhões.. todo o resto da sequência certinho, pô eu não tinha sido alfabetizado ainda.

​

Pintura

Tinha mais ou menos seis anos quando pintei minha primeira tela, era pequena, uns 20x20. Morávamos em Copacabana, e a Didi tinha uma amiga portuguesa que era pintora. Maria José assinava Maboin em suas telas. Não lembro do estilo, as achava bonitas e com vida. Nos reuníamos, eu, ela, Didi e Nádia que era minha irmã do meio.

Era uma cobertura na Rua Toneleros em Copacabana. Tinha muitas plantas, pinturas e tintas para todo lado. Assim que chegávamos, Maboin trazia dois cavaletes nos dava tela, tinta e pincéis, só assim poderia conversar em paz com Didi. Eram tardes alegres, mas de vez em quando a Nádia implicava com minhas pinturas, as dela eram todas certinhas, igual sua letra, que por sinal imitei, minhas pinturas não tinham regras, e sim rabiscos e cores, resumindo, eram abstratos.

A Nádia não entendia porque Maboin repetia "esse menino tem talento.

​

Saí um pouco do assunto, é verdade, mas vamos ao capricho. Eu e Didi tivemos que arregassar as mangas, tínhamos que bancas as nossas necessidades, minhas irmãs mais velhas estavam na faculdade, e começamos decorando cabides. Comprávamos o cabide de madeira, colávamos espuma com cola hélion e íamos com fita e cordões coloridos até o aro de arame. O trabalho era muito minucioso, e se não tivéssemos o máximo de capricho, tínhamos que refazer tudo, como moradores de copa, íamos sempre a praia , e reparamos que as cangas eram muito comuns, e invetamos várias estampas e processos de decorá-las. Sucesso total.
name: Helio Tattoo

bio:
Lea a self taught artist, born & raised in a small town on the east rand of Gauteng, Nigel. Art was always a passion of hers, growing up she was always found with pencil & paper in hand...her love of tattoos had sprung up from the first tattoo she ever got when she was 16...she started doing research on tattooing for the next 8 years; she crammed all the information she could about tattooing into her mind. 
By the time she had decided to pursue a career in the fine art of tattooing, her spouse at the time was heavily set against it...she endured and finally after 12 years of dreaming it, it became a reality...
Lea found two artists in PE willing to help guide her and so her journey began...NOW was the time to start applying all the information she had gathered over the years and the guidance of one of the greater artists in PE at the time. 
Lea started tattooing at the age of 29 and hasn't looked back since.
With a willingness to learn new trends and styles, Lea is ready to make her mark.

address: 207 Bui Vien, Ho chi minh, Vietnam
bio: My name is Richard, I'm from the philippines and have been a freelance artist for bout 17 years, specialising in charcoal art and portraiture. My love for art stems from when I was a kid, my parents put me in to a special art school to Foster my talents and I continued to grow as an artist from there. I then moved to Vietnam with my wife for her to take a job at the American International school and came across the most exciting opportunity I have ever had, to study as an apprentice under an incredible tattoo artist at exile Ink, a British owned studio in D2. I now currently work with another outstanding artist at Bob Tattoo studio on bui Vien, hcmc, where I have further developed my skills in the art of tattoo. We specialise in portrait and realism, but I also love to work with geometric and polynesian art. I have an avid interest in music and have become fascinated with the sound wave tattoo, I love that you can represent a memorable song or a loved ones voice with a piece of art on your skin.

address: L-7, RH-2, Sector 6, Vashi,, Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra
bio:
Namaste 
​
I am Vigneshkumar Shiva - An eternal seeker & follower of Hindu Dharma. I try to spread the knowledge of this Ancient way of Life through my Artworks.
​
AngaKala 108 also known as Tattoo Temple 108 is my vibration out to the Universe. 
​
I have spent as many years reading scriptures & understanding their fundamental teachings as i have in perfecting my visualization & art techniques. I have been drawing since was 5 years old & professionally tattooing since 2010.
​
I believe Tattoos have special powers if they are done a specific manner. They can affect the collector & audience in profound ways. They are excellent instruments of therapy, self development & even time travel.
​
I believe in collaborating with my clients &  focus on the emotion i'd like my artwork to inspire. I usually oblige when the concept is interesting but have to admit that  spiritual, fantasy, & comic art are what i love doing most.
​
I like to custom design each tattoo keeping in mind the concept, body part , skin tone & personality of the person that will get inked.​

bio: Established in 2013, DERMAPUNCT TATTOO is a private custom tattoo studio located in the scenic Hudson Valley area of NY.  The studio is owned by Jacqsun Jones, who has been tattooing for 13 years.  The studio is only open to clients and their guests during appointments so there are no distractions for the client or the artist, the whole experience is one on one from beginning to end.  Cleanliness is the owner's main priority.  As such, DERMAPUNCT offers a 100% disposable setup.  The artist also wears disposable sleeves and apron during the tattoo process.  Many of the Google reviews for DERMAPUNCT TATOO reiterate the private and serene nature of the studio as well as the high attention to detail in providing the safest procedure imaginable.  For more information go to wwww.dermapunct.com or @dermapunct on Instagram.

address: 805 6th ave se suite E, decatur, al
bio:
Zeb Wray is a native of Alabama. Born in Tuscumbia, he showed a strong interest in art at an early age by beginning to draw while in elementary school. As an adult, Zeb maintains his artistic direction by continually working and gaining education in both art and design related fields.

He has an Associate Degree in Graphic Design and Animation and has been Tattooing since 2009. Zeb specializes in Realism: Black and Grey/Color, Traditional, and Neo-Traditional tattoos.

He is very detail-specific and a perfectionist at giving a client want they want or showing them different ways to design a better tattoo for them. Zeb also attends Tattoo Conventions and travels to different shops for Tattoo Guest Spots occasionally.
name: zebulun Wray

bio:
I am a skilled artist highly trained in scalp micropigmentation (Hair Tattoo) and have been trained by world leaders in my industry. I enjoy making a difference into people's lives. I opened my clinic in Broadstairs Kent just offering bespoke treatments. Why Sound wave tattoos ? my purpose is to offer unique and specialist treatments. 
We offer scalp micropigmentation (Hair Tattoo) , sound wave tattoos, and tattoo removal. 
 My interest in sound wave tattoos has come from keep sakes as my wife makes jewellery for people that have newly borns or have lost loved ones. 

I want to offer the same as it has meaning and should be memorable and personal to you as it is with you for life. We only do the soundwave nothing too fancy.  

I look forward to meeting you.

address: 125 S State Street Suite C, Greenfield, IN
bio:
Amy has been tattooing since 2001. She studied Fine Arts at Vincennes University and did her apprenticeship with Kenny Sloan. She has worked in Indianapolis, IN, Greenfield IN, Fortvill,e IN, Pigeon Forge, TN,  Avon IN and Anderson IN.  She is excited to be located in her hometown of Greenfield Indiana once again in a shop she can call her own. Amy enjoys doing a variety of styles, small scale pieces with big meanings behind them, sleeves, back pieces, and always enjoys the challenge of a cover up. Most of all Amy enjoys getting to know her clients and the stories and meaning behind their artwork. She is always humbled when someone chooses her to be their artist.  
To schedule an appointment with Amy, you must speak to her directly.

bio:
Everyone has a story right? You bet, Some cool, Some funny, Some tragic. Legend’s is one that you just gotta hear in person over a bottle of Tequila and a nice campfire... His travels have taken him coast to coast more than once, allowing him to call TN, NM, AL, AR, CA, AZ, TX and a few other places home. He has been in and out of the tattoo industry since 1992 and has worked at some very cool very artistic shops, and some not so good shops. He has personally owned 3 tattoo shops, and a sign business. Father to four interesting and weird kids, and now a grandfather as well... He’s had his tragedies as well, Loss, Sorrow, Regret. But thru it all he has done his best to not let the tragedies of his past kill his drive and desire to create. Now there may be some stories people tell about him, people who will say anything to get you to ignore his artwork. But doesn't that happen everywhere? People who try to drag others down? That right there should say enough. He never lies about the things that have been, his intentions in life or what he does, and maintains a level of professionalism that is hard to do in today's world with facebook bullies and just plain old stupid people...... Check out his art, invite him to a conversation, you might just be surprised at the person you meet. Continuing to grow and learn and just be a decent father and friend to those friends he has, Legend will always give people a minute of his time to say hi or check out some art or even hear a story... As they say, Haters will be Haters..... Hope to see you in the chair sometime.... Have fun, smile when you can, laugh when you can’t, lift up the fallen and the broken and simply put... LIVE LIFE......
“Beware of Artists for they are most dangerous, They mix with ALL classes of society” ~~Queen Victoria....
Thanks for stopping by.. Peace....

A good tattoo artist needs to have a spark within him and Mr. Warman helped to ignite the spark in our founder and hence resulted in opening a tattoo studio. When you desire to get a tattoo, you undergo a long process of visualization and when that is realized it’s a joy that knows no bounds. We always strive to bring that one impeccable smile on client’s face, which speaks of their satisfaction. And our that’s in our motto in KDz tattoo studio.

We at KDz tattoo studio offer customization of designs, you can always walk in with any concept and we would confidently shape it into reality.

We at our tattoo studio make our best efforts to become Best Tattoo studio, and Best Tattoo shop in Delhi & Gurgaon. bio:
I started my apprenticeship Feb. 2015 & received my NH Practitioner License 2017.  I have been tattooing well over 2 yrs at Mayhem Ink LLC in Nashua NH. During my long & hard apprenticeship I was lucky to have numerous tattoo artist with years (15 plus) of experience to offer me. 
My favorite tattoo art is New Skool where my imagination runs wild creating some sick art work.  What am I most grateful for? Having a new apprentice in the shop :)  Actually, it is to be lucky enough to bring my art to life in form of a tattoo & make a living at something I love!  Art, Tattooing, & working with our clients!  Thanks for reading.  Katie

bio:
Beginning at the age of 14 ( in 1981) Johnny has been getting and doing tattoos.
Starting his career professionally at Shaw’s tattoo in 92, Johnny quickly began to make his name known. Many elite professionals have sought out Johnny’s services dating back to the 90’s when he tattooed Shaq while he worked at shows tattoo, doing his superman tattoo and then again in 92 he designed the TWISM tattoo for him. Members of Triple six mafia ,followed as well as Piggy D ,Rob Zombies guitarist,and later Johnny was tattooing many of the Houston Texans football players. Arian Foster ,Steve Slaton, Owen Daniels,Glover Quinn. His greatest honor was inking on The World Famous Enigma when he filled in the puzzle pieces across his chest area.

AWARD WINNING ARTIST

Johnny has won over 100 awards over an 8 year run at southern conventions. He has hosted many guests at his studio in Houston Texas. This rise of popularity sparkled into Texas Body Art’s golden reputation that now is a reflection of many years of hard work and discipline. People rely on dependability and moral in doing business.

Johnny also owns Biolab Piercing studio in Houston Texas located next door to Texas Body Art. Landmarking it as Houston only stand alone licensed and certified piercing studio in Houston. Johnny’s studio has been awarded by the USBA as Houston best tattoo studio in Houston for 10 consecutive years in a row. Inducted into the small business Hall of Fame. Enjoy the gallery and get in touch with us and set up an appointment or consult with Johnny today! 281-894-2282

SCHEDULING AN APPOINTMENT

JOHNNY WORKS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY

Consults can be done in email and text but deposits MUST BE MADE IN PERSON WITH CASH.If I decide to take on your project I will be in contact, as you will then need to secure your appt. with a $100 deposit and when I receive deposit we will move forward.

Pricing can not be discussed over the Internet as there are many factors to consider for proper pricing of a tattoo. Such as details in final design choice and colors.as well as placement.
(rates are 150 hourly) minimum on custom work is 2 hours
After initial consultation deposit is final you will be contacted again to set a date. Typical wait is 1 to 3 weeks preparation time on most designs

bio:
India's first Award-winning, internationally experienced artist Lokesh who has worked at places like California, New York, Texas, Massachusetts,  Amsterdam, Switzerland, Sweden, Germany, Italy, Denmark and Paris in few of the best tattoo studios that ever existed on this planet like Paul Booth's Last rites Tattoo theatre, NY, Tommy Lee's Monsters under your bed, Cologne, Germany, Alex de Pase's Off the map, Italy, Alla prima inks/John Montgomery's The grand tattoo lodge, CA, Off the map, MA, is a veteran tattoo artist who was also one of the first people to start tattooing in India. But the journey has not been easy for him. He began his pursuit at nineteen. An MBA by qualification, he strove hard to purchase the gear, even taking up a part-time position of a DJ at a local bar.

Lokesh is a self-trained artist and travels all across the world to work at different shops and to attend tattoo conventions. Ever since he can remember, he has been fascinated with sketching. His exceptional gift, and him treasuring it in return, brought to him audience and prizes. At fourteen, he won the 1st prize in the Inter-Asia level painting competition in Japan, organised by Mitsubishi.

With a little help from willing and curious friends, not to mention his own physical self (he displays an almost mystifying ambigram on his left arm which is also the first tattoo he ever did) Lokesh set off to conquer the Art. Day and night of practice, search of ideas, commitment and resolve yielded their rewards. It would produce an amalgam of tattoo styles, ranging from traditional to new school and portraits. Personally, Lokesh enjoys realistic tattooing the most and specialises in Color and Black and grey.

Call us at 0091-9810364801or e-mail us at devilztattooz@gmail.com to book an appointment with Lokesh at our studio in GK1
name: Lokesh Devil'z tattooz

bio: Mein Name ist Loli. Ich habe mich im Jahr 2010 mit meinem Inkredible Tattooshop selbständig gemacht. Mit viel Liebe und viel Spaß arbeite ich seit 2007 auf diesem Beruf und könnte mir nichts anderes mehr vorstellen. Bereits mit 11 Jahren wusste ich, dass ich meine Erfüllung im Piercen und Tätowieren finden werde als ich das erste mal einem Tätowierer über die Schulter schauen durfte. Nach meiner abgeschlossenen Lehre im Detailhandel habe ich sofort einen Platz zur Ausbildung als Piercerin gesucht und gefunden. In Zürich arbeitete ich 1 Jahr und war dort Filialleiterin, nachdem ich meine Ausbildung abschloss wechselte ich das Studio und habe mir noch mehr beibringen lassen von einem super Team. 2013 habe ich mir dann das Tätowieren selbst beigebracht und habe so meine Abwechslung zum Piercen gefunden. 2015 habe ich meinen Shop vergrößert, mein Sortiment an Schmuck so wie auch neues an Accessoires und cooler Kleidung angeschafft Farbe auf der Haut verändert die Hautfarbe und nicht die Persönlichkeit.

bio: Professional Tattoo and Bodypiercing since 1990. Da più di vent'anni Kaifa's Studio è presente a Torino come una realtà solida che nel tempo è riuscita a mantenersi costante nel proporre le migliori soluzioni nel campo di tattoo e del piercing. La nostra storia è cominciata con la passione e con la voglia di fornire agli appassionati di quest'arte una qualità particolare, andando oltre i soggetti del catalogo offrendo ai clienti la massima unicità di ogni pezzo realizzato. Il tatuaggio per noi è una disciplina che inizia dallo studio e dalla tecnica per arrivare alla sperimentazione artistica. Ogni disegno è personalizzato e creato attraverso un'accurata progettazione manuale perfezionata successivamente in computer grafica. Questo metodo innovativo ci consente di ottenere un tatuaggio più preciso ed armonico, perfettamente proporzionato al corpo.Non c'è uno stile che privilegiamo: tatuaggi tribali, maori, giapponesi o ritratti; ogni tatuaggio è un pezzo unico creato secondo le esigenze della persona che lo richiede ed interpretato dalla creatività del tatuatore che lo realizza. Il nostro staff ha competenze tecnico-artistiche e igienico-sanitarie, tutti gli strumenti utilizzati per piercing e tattoo vengono sempre sterilizzati in autoclave. Nato grazie alla passione di Claudio per il tatuaggio e il piercing, Kaifa's Studio ad oggi è il risultato della sua esperienza e della sua professionalità che negli anni ha portato all'accrescimento della crew. Tutti professionisti ed apprendisti che con amore si dedicano ogni giorno allo studio e all'applicazione di queste antiche arti, compagne nei secoli del corpo e dello spirito degli uomini.

bio:
Professional Tattoo Artist since 1996, Professional Body piercer since 1994.

I also have been doing various other body modifications on Body Mod Lovers across the globe such as Branding and Scarification (cutting) since 1994.

I have worked at various studios across the United States and I am very grateful for the many people I have got to not only work on, but also to get to know and help with there transitions in life.

Attended The Fakir Musafar Body Piercing Intensive in January 1999 to better improve my skills in my beloved industry, 
Also attending several seminars and training courses ranging from various teachings for Tattooing, Body Piercing, Branding, Scarification, First Aid, OSHA and Bloodborne Pathogens Training.

I have learned a lot in this journey of life and I have made a lot of changes in myself and the way I live day to day. I plan to continue on a positive Path and learn as much as I possibly can!

I am currently located in Osceola, IN. And working out of Crowned Raven Tattoo, Inc. with my partners.

bio: Nadia Denelzen Cooper had a gift for art that started at an early age. With her talent and ever growing passion for the form, she went on to study Fine Arts at the Ontario College of Art and Design, and graduated with a Degree of Fine Arts in 2006. Wanting to share her art using more than just brush and paper, she continued her education by completing a two year tattoo & piercing apprenticeship in 2011, further developing her talents on the human canvas. Now, at her own bright and inviting studio called The Ink Gallery, Nadia continues to build on her highly regarded reputation for delivering stunning pieces that wow her ever growing clientele. She is accomplished in a wide variety of artistic styles and works with many different mediums. Her sought after time is spent creating works of art for clients through custom tattoo designs, portraits, murals and commissions of fine art.

bio:
Hallo liebe Tattoofreunde, wir das Team von TattooDrive sind bereits seit 2013 als Tätowierer tätig.

Unsere Hauptspezialisierung sind die Polka Trash Tattoos sowie Soundwave´s.

Qualität ist uns sehr wichtig und diese möchten wir natürlich bei jedem unserer Kunden zeigen. Wir haben kein eigenes Studio sondern arbeiten bei uns zu Hause, natürlich wird dort nicht auf der Sofa oder ähnliches tätowiert, sondern wir arbeiten mit einem professionellem Equipment. Die Arbeitsgeräte und Materialien sind alle sauber und steril und die Tattoonadeln sind original verpackt bis der Kunde bei uns ist. Und was natürlich auch sehr wichtig ist das wir dadurch preiswerter sein können als die Berliner Tattoostudios. Unsere Kunden lieben die private Atmosphäre die bei uns herrscht und fühlen sich gleich von Anfang an Pudelwohl.

Wenn wir dein Interesse geweckt haben dann schreibt uns doch gerne.

bio:
I have been tattooing for about 3 years, and have been an artist all my life. My favorite tattoo styles are blackwork, and micro tatts, and my favorite art styles are psychedelic and Impressionism. 
I love to draw and paint, watercolor is my favorite medium to use when not tattooing. 
I am Buddhist, and my shop is based on Buddhist principles and the Eightfold Path. The goal of my work and my business is to give back to my local community and charitable organizations through tattooing, whenever possible. I absolutely love the concept of Sound tattoos, and cannot wait to begin working on them.

address: 1641 Bruce Smith Parkway, West Plains, MIssouri
bio:
Born October 9, 1973 in Coatsville, Pennsylvania of Kenneth Earl McHenry and Darlene Marie Dyabelko 
McHenry. At the early age of 1, Michael's parents divorced leaving him raised in part by his grandparents Harry 
Conrad and Ella Irma McHenry of Pheonixville Pa. The family moved to the Elverson, Pa. area in 1976. Here 
Michael attended the Twin Valley School District until the eighth grade. He won many awards through grade school 
clearly revealing his talent in the art field.
From Elverson, Michael moved to western Pennsylvania with his father for a brief 2 years. He attended Jamestown 
Jr Sr High school where he continued winning art awards in the county fair and state competitions. A pastel piece 
won first place in area, county, and regional competitions, later placing second in a state competition and landing the 
piece in the Reading Art Museum. Michael was the youngest in the competition ranging from 13 to 18 year old 
artists.
Before starting the 10th grade, Michael moved to Annville, Pa. and was raised to adulthood by Michael and 
Kathleen Dyabelko, his uncle and aunt. He proved his talent worthy of recognition numerous times by winning local 
competitions and displaying his art in shows as well as being voted class artist by the class of 1991. Michael 
continued his education by winning a full scholarship to Bradley Academy for the Visual Arts, overcoming nearly 
400 applicants from multiple eastern states.
He worked as an artist for Hershey Entertainment and Resort Company from 1990 until 1994. In 1993 Michael began a tattoo apprenticeship at a local parlor. In late 1994, Michael opened his first tattoo studio in Williamstown PA. Separate from the Tattoo Studio, he also
began Studio 1900. The "1900" represents his initials (MCM) in Roman Numerals. A signature trademark he has 
been using since age 14. In conjunction with award winning tattoos and a successful line of Flash designs in the early 2000's, Michael has produced custom oil paintings, portraits and various advertising art 
successfully ever since. All the hard work thrust Michael 
into the "lime light". He won numerous awards at shows and competitions and has sold his tattoo designs and 
artwork internationally and in 41 of the 50 United States. Being published in different magazines, and featured in 
many TV appearances, Michael has attracted clients from all around the country as well as from Canada, Mexico, 
England, Germany, Italy, and most recently, Japan.
In 2009, Michael returned to school to pursue a Bachelor of Arts degree. He relocated to his vacation state of 
Missouri in 2011 and began to teach part time. Graduating Magna Cum Laude class of 2013, he started his
teaching career by substitute teaching nearly full time, all grades and subjects for 2 years. In 2013 he began full time 
teaching at Rivendale Institute in Springfield, MO. Here he worked with autistic and emotionally distressed children. 
In 2014 Michael began teaching art in the Eminence R-I School district, teaching Pre-K through 12th grade.
In mid 2015, Michael returned full time to the tattoo industry and the convention circuit. You can see him occasionally sharing a booth with famed artist Judy Parker and hanging with the likes of Gil Monte and even Lyle Tuttle. Michael is married and has four beautiful children, two of which are diagnosed with Asperger Syndrome, instilling in 
him the drive to work with Autistic children, and the patience to tattoo even the most frightened or jittery clients.
name: Michael McHenry

Kathleen Dyabelko, his uncle and aunt. He proved his talent worthy of recognition numerous times by winning local 
competitions and displaying his art in shows as well as being voted class artist by the class of 1991. Michael 
continued his education by winning a full scholarship to Bradley Academy for the Visual Arts, overcoming nearly 
400 applicants from multiple eastern states.
He worked as an artist for Hershey Entertainment and Resort Company from 1990 until 1994. In 1993 Michael began a tattoo apprenticeship at a local parlor. In late 1994, Michael opened his first tattoo studio in Williamstown PA. Separate from the Tattoo Studio, he also
began Studio 1900. The "1900" represents his initials (MCM) in Roman Numerals. A signature trademark he has 
been using since age 14. In conjunction with award winning tattoos and a successful line of Flash designs in the early 2000's, Michael has produced custom oil paintings, portraits and various advertising art 
successfully ever since. All the hard work thrust Michael 
into the "lime light". He won numerous awards at shows and competitions and has sold his tattoo designs and 
artwork internationally and in 41 of the 50 United States. Being published in different magazines, and featured in 
many TV appearances, Michael has attracted clients from all around the country as well as from Canada, Mexico, 
England, Germany, Italy, and most recently, Japan.
In 2009, Michael returned to school to pursue a Bachelor of Arts degree. He relocated to his vacation state of 
Missouri in 2011 and began to teach part time. Graduating Magna Cum Laude class of 2013, he started his
teaching career by substitute teaching nearly full time, all grades and subjects for 2 years. In 2013 he began full time 
teaching at Rivendale Institute in Springfield, MO. Here he worked with autistic and emotionally distressed children. 
In 2014 Michael began teaching art in the Eminence R-I School district, teaching Pre-K through 12th grade.
In mid 2015, Michael returned full time to the tattoo industry and the convention circuit. You can see him occasionally sharing a booth with famed artist Judy Parker and hanging with the likes of Gil Monte and even Lyle Tuttle. Michael is married and has four beautiful children, two of which are diagnosed with Asperger Syndrome, instilling in

bio:
Fox was born in Colorado, but raised most of his life here in North Texas. Growing up in a construction family, he developed the eye and hand for accuracy and detail.
At 19, in fascination with the world of Body Modifications, he sought out to find a quality studio that would offer him a piercing apprenticeship. He completed a 6 month long apprenticeship in a great studio in Iowa. Fox continued to pierce and undergo education about more extreme modifications like branding, scarification, etching and trans/sub-dermal implants. After 4 years, thousands of piercings, and hundreds of extreme modifications, he decided it was time to expand his experience and found a studio in Tucson, Arizona that was offering a well rounded tattoo apprenticeship. Moving back to Texas for family, Fox took a spot in a shady shop in which his equipment and portfolio were destroyed. To recompose his life, he took a short hiatus from the tattoo life and returned to the construction industry.
Fox then found his wife Stephanie and has been set on fire to return to the artist's chair and change the scene in North Texas, which it is desperately in need of.

address: 226 Shepherds Hill Road, Bellevue Heights, SA
bio:
Hi there, my name is Lampin and while I have been tattooing for over 12 years I have been an artist for as long as I could hold a crayon.
Deeply passionate about art, you could say obsessed... but for me it's just my natural state of mind. To find beauty in all things designed... and everything is. I consider tattooing to be the art platform with the most responsibly and to hold the most honour. My motivation to open my own studio is to create the most relaxed, nurturing and fun environment for all artists from different backgrounds to learn this truly magical art. 

Let all be inspired 
Let all be free
For the love of art

Lampin

address: via C. Bedone n° 29, Meina, Piemonte
bio:
L'attività nasce dalla passione di Rudy per il tatuaggio nel 1990 a Meina (Novara).
Nel 1992 si iscrive a "THE AMSTERDAM TATTOO FOUNDATION", nel 1994 come 8° membro alla T.I.P.A(Tatuatori Italiani Professionisti Associati),
nel 2002 si iscrive alla T.A.I (Associazione Nazionale Tatuatori Artisti Italiani), oltre ad aver sostenuto un corso per la corretta pratica del piercing.
A differenza di quanto dichiarato da alcuni cosiddetti "colleghi" Rudy è stato veramente il primo ad iniziare l'attività in provincia di NOVARA e del V.C.O
e tutt' ora con 27 Anni reali di esperienza alle spalle si dedica con passione e professionalità sia nel tatuaggio che nel piercing,
seguendo scrupolosamente le linee guida del decreto Sanitario della Regione Piemonte elencate nel Bollettino Ufficiale Regionale -Parte I e II numero 22-
29 maggio 2003.
Lo studio e il lavoro svolto sono stati riconosciuti idonei dall'Azienda Sanitaria Locale (ASLL 13 NOVARA con sede ad Arona).

bio:
Hi My name is Duncan Stone. I have been tattooing for 20 years in Basingstoke. I have my own shop. I am 49 years old. I work with a great team of professionals and have gained a great reputation for quality tattooing in our area.
In our shop we have separate  private tattooing booths. This way we can ensure the privacy for all our Soundwave clients. 
I can see that the skin motion app is a great new modern idea that will be very popular.  I hope to produce highly detailed, clean and crisp Soundwaves in a hygienic, friendly and sometimes sympathetic environment. For more info about our studio: www.area51.co.uk

bio:
Lee Ozeki received his first tattoo at the age of 14 and has been hooked ever since. He has been tattooing for 5 years now, specializing in colour but with a passion for every style and technique.Â 
Lee served 5 years in the Canadian military, during which time he received a Bachelor's degree in Technology, and attended many fine arts courses. 
He attributes much of his success to his grandparents, who raised him from a young age and have always shown a tremendous amount of support for his interests. 
In his free time, Lee enjoys hiking, travelling, photography and anything that will get his blood racing. So feel free to drop in a line in his social media or contact Body Mods Studio.

bio:
Hello! I'm Wolf Chi and thank you for viewing my profile ; - ) I'm a tattoo artist working at Belleza tattoo studio located in New Taipei city, Taiwan. I have 3+ years tattoo experience and my favorites are realism and illustrative tattoo styles as well as small and decorative individuals. 
I believe every tattoo has a story hidden behind it, and I'm attracted to the idea of the sound wave tattoo because of it's personal value and the evolutionary idea that connects tattoo- as a hand-made art piece with the digital world.
As a traveler and a wonderor, if you wish to own a sound wave tattoo and just happen to be in Taiwan- the Formosa island- I would be very glad to realize your new tattoo for sure!

bio:
Since 2005 Kevin Stewart has dedicated himself to researching the latest developments in body modification. He has worked with medical professionals, fellow artists, and pioneers in technology to build a knowledge base and skill set that is unparalleled.

In 2014, he established Evolutionary Studios. Here, with the advancement of body-modification as his primary goal, Kevin continues to develop new procedures and techniques to pass on to the next generation of tattoo and body piercing artists.

Evolutionary Studios has since received multiple awards for body-art and business practices, including Best Tattoo Studio in Middle Tennessee.
name: Kevin Stewart

bio: A native of Northwest Indiana, Emilio Saylor is an extremely versatile artist, working across multiple medias with his art. Widely considered one of the top tattooers in the Midwest, Emilio has over a decade of experience in the tattoo industry at different shops in Northwest Indiana. He also has plenty of time put in on the tattoo convention circuit around the United States, racking up an impressive list of awards. Recently he has created his own blackwork style, but also has a very distinct new school flair. Emilio can flex to traditional, black and grey portraits, and quite literally everything between. He is sponsored by Electric Ink and has been published seven times in six different tattoo-specific magazines.

address: 3460 Oakdale Road, Suite D, Modesto , California
bio:
Angela started tattooing in 2002, and after a short apprenticeship owned and operated Immortal Ink Tattoo in Sonora for over 8 years.
 
In 2010, she took a break from tattooing to spend time with her kids and focus on being a mom of 2 awesome boys. Now that they are a little older, she tattoos by appointment only.
 
With a street shop background, she is able to take on most designs and styles of tattooing. She does a lot of detailed color work, but can also do soft black and gray tattoos, bold solid blacks, and intricate ornamental designs. She also has a lot of experience in cover-ups and rework of old tattoos.
name: Angela Adams
